forms.name: Bulbasaur
forms.entry: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

forms.name: Ivysaur
forms.entry: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

forms.name: Venusaur
forms.entry: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

forms.name: Charmander
forms.entry: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

forms.name: Charmeleon
forms.entry: Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When excited, it may blow out bluish-white flames.

forms.name: Charizard
forms.entry: When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tails burns more intensely.

forms.name: Squirtle
forms.entry: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

forms.name: Wartortle
forms.entry: When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull it in, but its tail will stick out a little bit.

forms.name: Blastoise
forms.entry: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.

forms.name: Caterpie
forms.entry: If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will release a horrible stink to protect itself.

forms.name: Metapod
forms.entry: Hardens its shell to protect itself. However, a large impact may cause it to pop out of its shell.

forms.name: Butterfree
forms.entry: Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.

forms.name: Weedle
forms.entry: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

forms.name: Kakuna
forms.entry: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

forms.name: Beedrill
forms.entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

forms.name: Pidgey
forms.entry: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

forms.name: Pidgeotto
forms.entry: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

forms.name: Pidgeot
forms.entry: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

forms.name: Rattata
forms.entry: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

forms.name: Rattata
forms.entry: It shows no interest in anything that isn't fresh. If you take it shopping with you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

forms.name: Raticate
forms.entry: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

forms.name: Raticate
forms.entry: This gourmet Pokémon is particular about the taste and freshness of its food. Restaurants where Raticate live have a good reputation.

forms.name: Spearow
forms.entry: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

forms.name: Fearow
forms.entry: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

forms.name: Ekans
forms.entry: The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

forms.name: Arbok
forms.entry: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

forms.name: Pikachu
forms.entry: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.

forms.name: Raichu
forms.entry: When electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.

forms.name: Raichu
forms.entry: It loves pancakes prepared with a secret Alolan recipe. Some wonder whether that recipe holds the key to this Pokémon's evolution.

forms.name: Sandshrew
forms.entry: When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.

forms.name: Sandshrew
forms.entry: Its ice-covered body lets it slide across the ground with bullet-like speed, sending its enemies flying when it hits them.

forms.name: Sandslash
forms.entry: Thanks to its thick claws, it's good at climbing trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park themselves in trees and go right to sleep.

forms.name: Sandslash
forms.entry: This is Sandslash's form after adaptation to a frigid environment. The cold air emitted by its body sharpens its icy spikes.

forms.name: Nidoran
forms.entry: A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware–its small horn secretes venom.

forms.name: Nidorina
forms.entry: When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

forms.name: Nidoqueen
forms.entry: Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

forms.name: Nidoran
forms.entry: The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

forms.name: Nidorino
forms.entry: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

forms.name: Nidoking
forms.entry: Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

forms.name: Clefairy
forms.entry: On every night of a full moon, groups of this Pokémon come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired Clefairy return to their quiet mountain retreats and go to sleep nestled up against each other.

forms.name: Clefable
forms.entry: According to tradition, people who see a pair of Clefable skipping by can look forward to a happy marriage.

forms.name: Vulpix
forms.entry: Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

forms.name: Vulpix
forms.entry: It looks like snow come to life, and the breath it exhales is −58 degrees Fahrenheit. Another name for it is Keokeo.

forms.name: Ninetales
forms.entry: According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

forms.name: Ninetales
forms.entry: The reason it guides people all the way down to the mountain's base is that it wants them to hurry up and leave.

forms.name: Jigglypuff
forms.entry: Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

forms.name: Wigglytuff
forms.entry: Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

forms.name: Zubat
forms.entry: Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

forms.name: Golbat
forms.entry: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

forms.name: Oddish
forms.entry: It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

forms.name: Gloom
forms.entry: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

forms.name: Vileplume
forms.entry: Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

forms.name: Paras
forms.entry: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

forms.name: Parasect
forms.entry: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushrooms on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

forms.name: Venonat
forms.entry: Its large eyes act as a radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

forms.name: Venomoth
forms.entry: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

forms.name: Diglett
forms.entry: Its head pokes up approximately eight inches out of the ground. However, its real size remains a mystery to this day.

forms.name: Diglett
forms.entry: After living in soil with high iron content for some time, three steel whiskers sprouted from the top of its head.

forms.name: Dugtrio
forms.entry: A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth of 60 miles. It's reported that this triggers an earthquake.

forms.name: Dugtrio
forms.entry: They're referred to as triplets, but they're not identical–the metallic elements in their bodies differ slightly. The proof shows in their whiskers!

forms.name: Meowth
forms.entry: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can't stop itself from picking them up.

forms.name: Meowth
forms.entry: Highly intelligent and prideful, it's famously difficult to handle–but that's also a reason for its popularity.

forms.name: Meowth
forms.entry: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon's body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.

forms.name: Persian
forms.entry: The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.

forms.name: Persian
forms.entry: Its round face is a symbol of wealth. Persian that have bigger, plumper faces are considered more beautiful.

forms.name: Psyduck
forms.entry: Appears unaware and totally vacant. However, if its chronic headache worsens, it starts exhibiting peculiar powers.

forms.name: Golduck
forms.entry: Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

forms.name: Mankey
forms.entry: An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

forms.name: Primeape
forms.entry: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

forms.name: Growlithe
forms.entry: A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

forms.name: Growlithe
forms.entry: They patrol their territory in pairs. The igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

forms.name: Arcanine
forms.entry: A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

forms.name: Arcanine
forms.entry: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

forms.name: Poliwag
forms.entry: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

forms.name: Poliwhirl
forms.entry: Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

forms.name: Poliwrath
forms.entry: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

forms.name: Abra
forms.entry: Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

forms.name: Kadabra
forms.entry: Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.

forms.name: Alakazam
forms.entry: If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that spoon is apparently delicious.

forms.name: Machop
forms.entry: Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.

forms.name: Machoke
forms.entry: The belt around its waist holds back its energy. Without it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.

forms.name: Machamp
forms.entry: With four arms, it can attack and defend simultaneously. It's said to have mastered every martial art in the world.

forms.name: Bellsprout
forms.entry: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

forms.name: Weepinbell
forms.entry: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

forms.name: Victreebel
forms.entry: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

forms.name: Tentacool
forms.entry: It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

forms.name: Tentacruel
forms.entry: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

forms.name: Geodude
forms.entry: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

forms.name: Geodude
forms.entry: Its stone head is imbued with electricity and magnetism. If you carelessly step on one, you'll be in for a painful shock.

forms.name: Graveler
forms.entry: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

forms.name: Graveler
forms.entry: They eat rocks and often get into a scrap over them. The shock of Graveler smashing together causes a flash of light and a booming noise.

forms.name: Golem
forms.entry: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it's exposed to air.

forms.name: Golem
forms.entry: It uses magnetism to accelerate and fire off rocks tinged with electricity. Even if it doesn't score a direct hit, the jolt of electricity will do the job.

forms.name: Ponyta
forms.entry: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

forms.name: Ponyta
forms.entry: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

forms.name: Rapidash
forms.entry: Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

forms.name: Rapidash
forms.entry: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

forms.name: Slowpoke
forms.entry: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

forms.name: Slowpoke
forms.entry: It uses its tail to fish, but the scent of the spice emanating from its tail ensures its catches are always lacking.

forms.name: Slowbro
forms.entry: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

forms.name: Slowbro
forms.entry: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

forms.name: Magnemite
forms.entry: It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.

forms.name: Magneton
forms.entry: When three Magnemite link together, their brains also become one. They do not become three times more intelligent.

forms.name: Farfetch'd
forms.entry: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

forms.name: Farfetch'd
forms.entry: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch'd that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.

forms.name: Doduo
forms.entry: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

forms.name: Dodrio
forms.entry: The three heads express joy, sorrow and anger as they plan strategy together. When it sleeps, one head remains awake.

forms.name: Seel
forms.entry: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

forms.name: Dewgong
forms.entry: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

forms.name: Grimer
forms.entry: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won't grow in its path.

forms.name: Grimer
forms.entry: Brought to Alola to solve the garbage problem, Grimer seems to relish any and all kinds of trash.

forms.name: Muk
forms.entry: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

forms.name: Muk
forms.entry: Muk's coloration becomes increasingly vivid the more it feasts on its favorite dish–trash.

forms.name: Shellder
forms.entry: Even when its shell is closed, its tongue still hangs out. If you give its tongue a good yank, the shock will cause Shellder to open its shell.

forms.name: Cloyster
forms.entry: Slowpoke tails are its favorite food. It has even been known to come up on land to look for Slowpoke from time to time.

forms.name: Gastly
forms.entry: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape as it appears to be made of a gas.

forms.name: Haunter
forms.entry: By licking, it saps the victim's life. It causes shaking that won't stop until the victim's demise.

forms.name: Gengar
forms.entry: It can pass through other dimensions and can appear anywhere. It caused a stir one time when it stuck just one leg out of a wall.

forms.name: Onix
forms.entry: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

forms.name: Drowzee
forms.entry: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

forms.name: Hypno
forms.entry: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

forms.name: Krabby
forms.entry: Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

forms.name: Kingler
forms.entry: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

forms.name: Voltorb
forms.entry: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

forms.name: Voltorb
forms.entry: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

forms.name: Electrode
forms.entry: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

forms.name: Electrode
forms.entry: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.

forms.name: Exeggcute
forms.entry: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

forms.name: Exeggutor
forms.entry: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

forms.name: Exeggutor
forms.entry: Alola is the best environment for this Pokémon. Local people take pride in its appearance, saying this is how Exeggutor ought to look.

forms.name: Cubone
forms.entry: Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.

forms.name: Marowak
forms.entry: Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.

forms.name: Marowak
forms.entry: It has transformed the spirit of its dear departed mother into flames, and tonight it will once again dance in mourning of others of its kind.

forms.name: Hitmonlee
forms.entry: When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.

forms.name: Hitmonchan
forms.entry: Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.

forms.name: Lickitung
forms.entry: Its tongue, twice its body's length, moves around freely to catch prey. Its licks cause a tingling sensation.

forms.name: Koffing
forms.entry: In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!

forms.name: Weezing
forms.entry: This Pokémon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.

forms.name: Weezing
forms.entry: This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.

forms.name: Rhyhorn
forms.entry: A Pokémon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won't stop running until it falls asleep.

forms.name: Rhydon
forms.entry: Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

forms.name: Chansey
forms.entry: A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.

forms.name: Tangela
forms.entry: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

forms.name: Kangaskhan
forms.entry: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

forms.name: Horsea
forms.entry: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

forms.name: Seadra
forms.entry: Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

forms.name: Goldeen
forms.entry: Spellbound by the length of its horn and the beauty of its fins, many strange Trainers raise Goldeen and nothing but Goldeen.

forms.name: Seaking
forms.entry: Trainers who are crazy for Seaking are divided into horn enthusiasts and fin enthusiasts. The two groups do not get along well.

forms.name: Staryu
forms.entry: This Pokémon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it's unconcerned by their snack attacks.

forms.name: Starmie
forms.entry: When away from human eyes, its core is said to glow mysteriously in seven colors. This Pokémon may have come from outer space.

forms.name: Mr. Mime
forms.entry: Always practices its pantomime act. It makes enemies believe something exists that really doesn't.

forms.name: Mr. Mime
forms.entry: Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.

forms.name: Scyther
forms.entry: Leaps out of tall grass and slices prey with its scythes. The movement looks like that of a ninja.

forms.name: Jynx
forms.entry: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

forms.name: Electabuzz
forms.entry: If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

forms.name: Magmar
forms.entry: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

forms.name: Pinsir
forms.entry: Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can't move if it's cold, so it lives in warm places.

forms.name: Tauros
forms.entry: A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won't stop until it hits something.

forms.name: Tauros
forms.entry: This Pokémon has a muscular body and excels at close-quarters combat. It uses its short horns to strike the opponent’s weak spots.

forms.name: Tauros
forms.entry: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.

forms.name: Tauros
forms.entry: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.

forms.name: Magikarp
forms.entry: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

forms.name: Gyarados
forms.entry: Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

forms.name: Lapras
forms.entry: A gentle soul that can understand human speech. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.

forms.name: Ditto
forms.entry: It transforms into whatever it sees. If the thing it's transforming into isn't right in front of it, Ditto relies on its memory—so sometimes it fails.

forms.name: Eevee
forms.entry: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee's genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

forms.name: Vaporeon
forms.entry: Its cell structure is similar to water molecules. It melts into the water and becomes invisible.

forms.name: Jolteon
forms.entry: A sensitive Pokémon that easily becomes sad or angry. Every time its mood changes, it charges power.

forms.name: Flareon
forms.entry: When it catches prey or finds berries, it breathes fire on them until they're well done, and then it gobbles them up.

forms.name: Porygon
forms.entry: The world's first artificially created Pokémon. It can travel through electronic space.

forms.name: Omanyte
forms.entry: An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

forms.name: Omastar
forms.entry: Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

forms.name: Kabuto
forms.entry: A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

forms.name: Kabutops
forms.entry: A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

forms.name: Aerodactyl
forms.entry: It flew through the open skies over the ancient continent as if they were its own. When it touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.

forms.name: Snorlax
forms.entry: It has no interest in anything other than eating. Even if you climb up on its stomach while it's napping, it doesn't seem to mind at all!

forms.name: Articuno
forms.entry: A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

forms.name: Articuno
forms.entry: Its feather-like blades are composed of psychic energy and can shear through thick iron sheets as if they were paper.

forms.name: Zapdos
forms.entry: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

forms.name: Zapdos
forms.entry: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 290 kph.

forms.name: Moltres
forms.entry: A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

forms.name: Moltres
forms.entry: This Pokémon's sinister, flame-like aura will consume the spirit of any creature it hits. Victims become burned-out shadows of themselves.

forms.name: Dratini
forms.entry: Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon's existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

forms.name: Dragonair
forms.entry: Some say that if you see it at the start of the year, flying through the sky and twisting its body, you'll be healthy all year long.

forms.name: Dragonite
forms.entry: You'll often hear tales of this kindhearted Pokémon rescuing people or Pokémon that are drowning.

forms.name: Mewtwo
forms.entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments. Its DNA is almost the same as Mew's. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

forms.name: Mew
forms.entry: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

forms.name: Chikorita
forms.entry: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.

forms.name: Bayleef
forms.entry: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.

forms.name: Meganium
forms.entry: Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed, just as if they were relaxing in a sunny forest.

forms.name: Cyndaquil
forms.entry: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

forms.name: Quilava
forms.entry: This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.

forms.name: Typhlosion
forms.entry: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

forms.name: Typhlosion
forms.entry: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. It is believed that its form was influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui's center.

forms.name: Totodile
forms.entry: It is small but rough and tough. It won't hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

forms.name: Croconaw
forms.entry: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

forms.name: Feraligatr
forms.entry: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

forms.name: Sentret
forms.entry: A very cautious Pokémon, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.

forms.name: Furret
forms.entry: There is no telling where the tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick at hunting Rattata.

forms.name: Hoothoot
forms.entry: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

forms.name: Noctowl
forms.entry: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

forms.name: Ledyba
forms.entry: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

forms.name: Ledian
forms.entry: The star patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

forms.name: Spinarak
forms.entry: The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web's strands.

forms.name: Ariados
forms.entry: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.

forms.name: Crobat
forms.entry: The transformation of its legs into wings made it better at flying, but more clumsy at walking.

forms.name: Chinchou
forms.entry: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

forms.name: Lanturn
forms.entry: This Pokémon uses the bright part of its body, which changed from a dorsal fin, to lure prey.

forms.name: Pichu
forms.entry: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

forms.name: Cleffa
forms.entry: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

forms.name: Igglybuff
forms.entry: Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously--anytime, anywhere.

forms.name: Togepi
forms.entry: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.

forms.name: Natu
forms.entry: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

forms.name: Xatu
forms.entry: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

forms.name: Mareep
forms.entry: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

forms.name: Flaaffy
forms.entry: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

forms.name: Ampharos
forms.entry: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

forms.name: Bellossom
forms.entry: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

forms.name: Marill
forms.entry: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.

forms.name: Azumarill
forms.entry: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

forms.name: Sudowoodo
forms.entry: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.

forms.name: Politoed
forms.entry: When it expands its throat to croak out a tune, nearby Poliwag and Poliwhirl gather immediately.

forms.name: Hoppip
forms.entry: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.

forms.name: Skiploom
forms.entry: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

forms.name: Jumpluff
forms.entry: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

forms.name: Aipom
forms.entry: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

forms.name: Sunkern
forms.entry: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.

forms.name: Sunflora
forms.entry: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

forms.name: Yanma
forms.entry: It can see in all directions without moving its big eyes, helping it spot attackers and food right away.

forms.name: Wooper
forms.entry: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

forms.name: Wooper
forms.entry: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

forms.name: Quagsire
forms.entry: This carefree Pokémon has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

forms.name: Espeon
forms.entry: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent's next move.

forms.name: Umbreon
forms.entry: On the night of a full moon, or when it gets excited, the ring patterns on its body glow yellow.

forms.name: Murkrow
forms.entry: It hides any shiny object it finds in a secret location. Murkrow and Meowth loot one another's stashes.

forms.name: Slowking
forms.entry: Every time it yawns, Shellder injects more poison into it. The poison makes it more intelligent.

forms.name: Slowking
forms.entry: It creates potions by mixing toxins with the food it’s eaten. Not even Slowking itself knows what effects the potions will have.

forms.name: Misdreavus
forms.entry: It loves to bite and yank people's hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.

forms.name: Unown
forms.entry: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.

forms.name: Wobbuffet
forms.entry: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

forms.name: Girafarig
forms.entry: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

forms.name: Pineco
forms.entry: It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

forms.name: Forretress
forms.entry: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

forms.name: Dunsparce
forms.entry: When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.

forms.name: Gligar
forms.entry: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.

forms.name: Steelix
forms.entry: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.

forms.name: Snubbull
forms.entry: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

forms.name: Granbull
forms.entry: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

forms.name: Qwilfish
forms.entry: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

forms.name: Qwilfish
forms.entry: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.

forms.name: Scizor
forms.entry: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

forms.name: Shuckle
forms.entry: The fluid secreted by its toes carves holes in rocks for nesting and can be mixed with Berries to make a drink.

forms.name: Heracross
forms.entry: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies then lifts and throws them.

forms.name: Sneasel
forms.entry: Vicious in nature, it drives Pidgey from their nests and feasts on the eggs that are left behind.

forms.name: Sneasel
forms.entry: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel's grasp.

forms.name: Teddiursa
forms.entry: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

forms.name: Ursaring
forms.entry: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen Berries.

forms.name: Slugma
forms.entry: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

forms.name: Magcargo
forms.entry: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

forms.name: Swinub
forms.entry: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

forms.name: Piloswine
forms.entry: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

forms.name: Corsola
forms.entry: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.

forms.name: Corsola
forms.entry: Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokémon, and it will curse you if you kick it.

forms.name: Remoraid
forms.entry: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

forms.name: Octillery
forms.entry: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow Octillery.

forms.name: Delibird
forms.entry: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

forms.name: Mantine
forms.entry: As it majestically swims, it doesn't care if Remoraid attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

forms.name: Skarmory
forms.entry: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

forms.name: Houndour
forms.entry: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

forms.name: Houndoom
forms.entry: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

forms.name: Kingdra
forms.entry: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

forms.name: Phanpy
forms.entry: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

forms.name: Porygon2
forms.entry: This upgraded version of Porygon is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.

forms.name: Stantler
forms.entry: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

forms.name: Smeargle
forms.entry: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

forms.name: Tyrogue
forms.entry: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

forms.name: Hitmontop
forms.entry: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.

forms.name: Smoochum
forms.entry: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

forms.name: Elekid
forms.entry: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.

forms.name: Magby
forms.entry: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

forms.name: Miltank
forms.entry: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

forms.name: Blissey
forms.entry: Anyone who takes even one bite of Blissey's egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

forms.name: Raikou
forms.entry: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

forms.name: Entei
forms.entry: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

forms.name: Suicune
forms.entry: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

forms.name: Larvitar
forms.entry: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

forms.name: Pupitar
forms.entry: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its Thrashing can topple a mountain.

forms.name: Tyranitar
forms.entry: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

forms.name: Lugia
forms.entry: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

forms.name: Ho-Oh
forms.entry: Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world's skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.

forms.name: Celebi
forms.entry: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
